# Accessibility (A11y)

- Follow `plugin:jsx-a11y/strict` rules from [eslint.config.mjs](mdc:eslint.config.mjs).
- Use semantic HTML elements (`<main>`, `<nav>`, `<header>`, `<footer>`, `<section>`, `<button>`, `<a>`).
- All interactive elements must be keyboard accessible; avoid `div`/`span` with click handlers.
- Provide meaningful `alt` text for images. Decorative images should use empty `alt`.
- Inputs and controls must have associated labels. Use `aria-*` attributes only when semantic HTML is insufficient.
- Links opening in new tabs must include `rel="noopener noreferrer"` when `target="_blank"`.
- Maintain visible focus outlines; do not remove focus styles without providing accessible alternatives.
- Ensure color contrast meets WCAG AA.

